Assume you have two data files: a personnel file with information about employees and a
second file withinformation about performance categories. You will use IBM SPSS Modeler
to merge the files together using performance category as the key. However, there are
inconsistencies in the category keys used in both the personnel file and the performance
file. Inorder to merge the files together without losing information from either the personnel
file or the performance category file, you would use:
A. A full outer join.
B. An inner join.
C. A partial outer join.
